fulltitle: Church Committee Hearings: FBI Abuses, MLK, COINTELPRO, and More
title: Church Committee Hearings: FBI Abuses, MLK, COINTELPRO, and More
_filename: _Church Committee Hearings - FBI Abuses, MLK, COINTELPRO, and More.webm
description:
Committee Counsels Frederick A.O. Schwarz and Curtis Smothers review Committee findings as to FBI abuses. FBI programs such as COINTELPRO are discussed, as well as the FBI's assault on the civil liberties of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. FBI efforts against the New Left and Women's Liberation groups are also discussed. This is the audio content of a public television show which aired at the time of the Senate Hearings.

From the AARC:

The Senate Select Committee to Study Governmental Operations with Respect to Intelligence Activities, known as the "Church Committee" after its chairman Frank Church, conducted a wide-ranging investigation of the intelligence agencies in the post-Watergate period.

The Church Committee took public and private testimony from hundreds of people, collected huge volumes of files from the FBI, CIA, NSA, IRS, and many other federal agencies, and issued 14 reports in 1975 and 1976.

For copies of the reports: http://www.aarclibrary.org/publib/church/reports/contents.htm

For more related content, please visit: https://archive.org/details/@altviewstv-fanclub
